sentences: Pierre-Alexandre Busson (born 3 June 1977) better known as Yuksek, is a French electronic music producer, remixer, singer and DJ.
After playing the piano for ten years at a conservatoire, he took part in several bands such as Klanguage, whose first album was released in 2007.

He created his first tracks as Yuksek in 2002 and then started to perform successfully as a DJ all over the world.
His debut album, Away from the Sea, was released on February 9, 2009.

Featuring the singles Tonight and Extraball, this album received a lot of media attention, including an interview on the popular French TV talk show Le Grand Journal on premium pay television channel Canal+.
Tonight was also selected as the soundtrack for the show in January 2009.

The first EP, EP#1 was released May 13, 2013.

Their first EP titled We’re Ready When You Are was released on May 17, 2010.
Since 2011, Yuksek has been collaborating with The Magician (aka Stephane Fassano, former member of Aeroplane) under the stage name Peter & The Magician.
Their first song "Twist" has been recorded on a Kitsuné compilation (Kitsuné Maison Compilation 11: "The Indie Dance Issue") released on May 26, 2011.
The three-track EP also called Twist was released one month later on the Kitsuné label.
The Alexanders released their debut single "Don't Miss" through Yuksek's label Partyfine on 24 February 2014.
